<p><strong>Last updated: March 2026</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>18 million American businesses use Google Business Profile.</strong> Those profiles generate 2 billion customer connections every month. GBP is the single most important local marketing asset a business can own.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Google Business Profile statistics reveal exactly how consumers find, evaluate, and choose local businesses. Every click, call, review, and direction request tells a story about buyer behavior. The businesses that understand these numbers outperform those that ignore them.</p>
<p>We compiled 50+ Google Business Profile statistics from Google, <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey/">BrightLocal</a>, <a href="https://birdeye.com/blog/state-of-google-business-profiles/">Birdeye</a>, Whitespark, and other industry sources. Every stat is sourced and dated.</p>
<p>Here are the categories covered:</p>
<ul>
<li>GBP usage and adoption</li>
<li>Engagement metrics (clicks, calls, impressions)</li>
<li>Reviews and trust signals</li>
<li>Photos and visual content impact</li>
<li>Local SEO ranking signals</li>
<li>Consumer behavior and search patterns</li>
</ul>
<h2>GBP Usage and Adoption Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>1. 18 million American businesses use Google Business Profile.</strong>
(Source: Google, 2025)
That covers roughly half of all U.S. businesses with employees.</p>
<p><strong>2. Only 64% of businesses have verified their Google Business Profile.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://birdeye.com/blog/state-of-google-business-profiles/">Birdeye</a>, 2025)
36% of businesses leave their profiles unverified. Unverified profiles rank lower and miss key features.</p>
<p><strong>3. Companies edit their Google Business Profiles 15 million times per month.</strong>
(Source: Google, 2025)
Active profile management is widespread among businesses that take <a href="/blog/local-seo-guide/">local SEO</a> seriously.</p>
<p><strong>4. 83% of property management companies have verified GBPs. That is the highest rate by industry.</strong>
(Source: Birdeye, 2025)
Property management leads all sectors in GBP adoption.</p>
<p><strong>5. Only 45% of automotive and home services businesses have verified GBPs. That is the lowest rate.</strong>
(Source: Birdeye, 2025)
The industries that benefit most from local search often have the lowest adoption rates.</p>
<p><strong>6. 60% of businesses have never posted on their Google Business Profile.</strong>
(Source: Birdeye, 2025)
Most businesses miss the engagement boost that <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">regular GBP posting</a> provides.</p>
<p><strong>7. 33% of verified profiles use Google Messages.</strong>
(Source: Birdeye, 2025)
Messaging adoption varies by industry. Legal (67%) and consumer goods (63%) lead.</p>
<p><strong>8. There are 4,039 Google Business Profile categories as of March 2026.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://daltonluka.com/blog/google-my-business-categories">Dalton Luka</a>, 2026)
Google updates categories frequently. Choosing the right primary category directly impacts ranking.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Google Business Profile usage and adoption statistics for 2026" src="/images/blog/gbp-usage-adoption-stats.webp" /></p>
