<h2>GBP and Local SEO Ranking Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>33. GBP signals account for 32% of local pack ranking factors.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://whitespark.ca/local-search-ranking-factors/">Whitespark</a>, 2025)
Your Google Business Profile carries the single largest weight in local search rankings.</p>
<p><strong>34. 75% of top-ranking pages have complete GBP descriptions.</strong>
(Source: Blogging Wizard, 2026)
Complete profiles outrank incomplete ones. Only 40% of positions 11 to 20 have complete descriptions.</p>
<p><strong>35. Businesses with complete profiles are 70% more likely to attract location visits.</strong>
(Source: Google, 2025)
Profile completeness is a direct ranking and conversion factor.</p>
<p><strong>36. Complete profiles are 50% more likely to lead to a purchase.</strong>
(Source: Google, 2025)
Half the battle is simply filling out every field. Many businesses skip optional sections.</p>
<p><strong>37. Complete profiles are 2.7 times more likely to be trusted by consumers.</strong>
(Source: Google, 2025)
Trust drives clicks. Clicks drive calls. Calls drive revenue.</p>
<p><strong>38. Businesses with complete profiles receive 7x more clicks.</strong>
(Source: Google, 2025)
A <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">fully optimized profile</a> is one of the highest-ROI marketing activities for any local business.</p>
<p><strong>39. Customers are 96% more likely to visit when business hours are displayed.</strong>
(Source: Google, 2025)
Missing hours is one of the most common and costly GBP mistakes.</p>
<p><strong>40. 76% of SEO professionals say GBP management is the most valuable local SEO service.</strong>
(Source: BrightLocal, 2025)
GBP outranks citation building (43%) and content creation (53%) for perceived local SEO value.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="GBP local SEO ranking factor statistics" src="/images/blog/gbp-local-seo-ranking-stats.webp" /></p>
<h2>Consumer Behavior and Local Search Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>41. 46% of all Google searches have local intent.</strong>
(Source: DemandSage, 2026)
Nearly half of all <a href="/blog/google-search-statistics/">Google searches</a> seek local information.</p>
<p><strong>42. 78% of local mobile searches result in an offline purchase within 24 hours.</strong>
(Source: DemandSage, 2026)
Local search drives real-world revenue faster than any other marketing channel.</p>
<p><strong>43. 88% of consumers who search locally on mobile visit or call a business within a day.</strong>
(Source: Google, 2025)
The intent behind local search is immediate and action-oriented.</p>
<p><strong>44. 64% of consumers use GBP to find contact details.</strong>
(Source: BrightLocal, 2025)
Your profile is often the first touchpoint between your business and a potential customer.</p>
<p><strong>45. 69% of consumers check business hours on GBP before visiting.</strong>
(Source: BrightLocal, 2025)
Accurate hours prevent lost customers who arrive to find a closed business.</p>
<p><strong>46. 50% of consumers use GBP for directions to a business.</strong>
(Source: BrightLocal, 2025)
<a href="/blog/google-maps-seo/">Google Maps SEO</a> is essential because half of GBP users move through directly to the location.</p>
<p><strong>47. 62% of consumers would avoid a business with incorrect information on its profile.</strong>
(Source: BrightLocal, 2025)
Wrong addresses, phone numbers, or hours actively drive customers to competitors.</p>
<p><strong>48. 16% of consumers encounter fake business listings every month.</strong>
(Source: BrightLocal, 2025)
51% have encountered a fake listing in the past year. Fake profiles erode trust in the entire ecosystem.</p>
<p><strong>49. 71% of GBP interactions come from mobile devices.</strong>
(Source: SeoProfy, 2025)
Mobile is the primary interface for local search. Your profile must look good on a phone screen.</p>
<p><strong>50. Voice-assisted searches account for 14% of mobile GBP accesses.</strong>
(Source: SeoProfy, 2025)
<a href="/blog/voice-search-seo/">Voice search</a> is a growing access point for Google Business Profiles.</p>
