<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How many businesses use Google Business Profile?</strong></p>
<p>18 million American businesses use Google Business Profile. That represents roughly half of all U.S. businesses with employees. Only 64% have verified their profiles, which means millions of businesses miss ranking features and full visibility.</p>
<p><strong>How many clicks does a Google Business Profile get?</strong></p>
<p>The average verified GBP receives approximately 200 clicks per month, including 105 website visits, 50 phone calls, and 66 direction requests. Profiles with complete information and 100+ photos see dramatically higher engagement.</p>
<p><strong>Do Google reviews affect local rankings?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Top-ranking local businesses average 47 reviews, compared to 39 for the average business. <a href="/blog/google-reviews-statistics/">Review volume</a>, recency (73% of consumers only trust reviews from the past month), and response rate all factor into local search rankings.</p>
<p><strong>How important are GBP photos for local SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Extremely important. Profiles with photos receive 42% more direction requests and 35% more website clicks. Businesses with 100+ photos see 520% more calls. Top-ranking profiles average 250 images. See our <a href="/blog/gbp-photos-guide/">GBP photo guide</a> for optimization tips.</p>
<p><strong>What percentage of local ranking depends on GBP?</strong></p>
<p>GBP signals account for 32% of local pack ranking factors, making it the single largest ranking factor. Profile completeness, reviews, photos, categories, and posting frequency all contribute to this 32% weight.</p>
<p><strong>How often should I update my Google Business Profile?</strong></p>
<p>At minimum, weekly. Post new content, respond to reviews, add photos, and update business information. 60% of businesses never post on their GBP. The businesses that post regularly outperform those that treat their profile as a set-and-forget listing.</p>
<p>Google Business Profile is the highest-ROI local marketing asset most businesses underuse. The data proves it. Complete profiles get 7x more clicks. Photos drive 42% more actions. Reviews influence 97% of consumers. The businesses that optimize their GBP now will capture the local search traffic that competitors leave on the table.</p>
